{
  "stem": "27340.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But unfortunately, that ship, which was a German ship, was in fact on the high seas when-- on the way to Southampton when Hitler-- sorry, when Chamberlain declared war on Germany on that fateful Sunday morning.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And naturally, it being a German ship, it went back to Hamburg.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It couldn't go to Southampton.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I understand that all these people who were on board, some 800 of-- or so of them, were all eliminated within a very, very short time.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't know that at the time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My friend didn't know it at the time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think he only found that out at the end of the war, when to some extent some of the pictures or some of the events became known.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, the war having started in '39, the Allies, as you know, didn't do too well.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Germans were incredibly successful, occupied France, occupied Belgium and occupied Holland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the British Expeditionary Force obviously had to fall back and ultimately ended up in this very glorious retreat of Dunkirk.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And because Margate was on the front line or very close to the Channel, Margate was one of the reception ports, if I can call it that, of troops coming over and disembarking in Margate.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they were received and taken care of by nurses and other volunteers, mainly female, many men as well.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And schoolchildren were asked to help as well.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And naturally, this seemed to be a wonderful chance for me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so I was seconded to a nurse.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And oddly enough, I was equipped with thousands of cigarettes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "In those days, everybody smoked Woodbines.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They came in small green packets.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And my task was to light a cigarette and then put it into the mouth of the oncoming soldier.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
